parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine head gasket failure can cause fluid leaks, engine overheating, and engine damage, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or fires.
Timing cover failure can cause oil to mix with antifreeze, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents or fires.
Engine stalling can cause a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Intermittent engine stalling at slow speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause damage, injury, or fatalities.
symptoms: often resulting in damage or loss of life.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the rear differential housing cover can cause fluid leaks, leading to premature wear on the differential components, and potentially causing loss of vehicle control or accidents.
Transmission slipping and failure can cause loss of power, stalling, or accidents, and may lead to costly repairs or even require replacement of the transmission.
Clutch malfunction can cause difficulty shifting, loss of power, or stalling, and may lead to accidents or costly repairs.
Driveshaft noise can be a sign of wear or damage to the driveshaft or related components, which can lead to premature wear or failure, and potentially cause loss of vehicle control or accidents.
Gear shift lever misalignment can cause difficulty shifting, loss of power, or stalling, and may lead to accidents or costly repairs.
symptoms: pops out of position when turning steering wheel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering linkage can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the steering wheel feels loose or free-wheeling
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the wheel shakes when crossing bumps in the road.
